- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper mentions using off-the-shelf tools for news analysis, which could fall under the sub-category of information retrieval. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper specifically applies the proposed approach to predict natural gas prices, which falls under the sub-category of computational finance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper's use of machine learning and natural language processing techniques could also fall under the broader sub-category of artificial intelligence.
